{
  "texts": [
    "The digest of the analysis results of the data and the1: Receive EMR from hospital database service 2: Hash the EM R p id with a hash function -→ Hash(EM R p id) 3: Create the diseaseDescription p id from EMR 4: if EM R p id is sensitive then 5: block size = 4 6: else 7: block size = 128 8: end if 9: for i ← 0, size(EM R p id)/block size do 10: f ragment i = splitF ile(EM R p id, block size) 11: create the symmetric key -→ secretKey i 12:crypt the f ragment i by using the secretKey i -→ encrpyted f ragmenti = f ragment (i)secretKeyi 13:save the encrpyted f ragmenti to distiributed database 14:add the addresses of encrpyted f ragmenti and secretKey i to the storage list 15:crypt the storage list by using the p id privateKey -→ encrpytedStorageList p id = storagelist p id privateKey 16: end for 17: Save blok id, p id, Hash(EM R p id), timestamp, encrpytedStorageList p id, diseaseDescription p id, previous block hash to the blockchain as a new block address of the symmetric key are saved in a block on the blockchain and shared with the patient.",
    "After the thirdparty entity analysis of a patient EMR, the EMR data are hashed and compared to the hash value on the blockchain.If the hash values are not equal, the data have been modified.",
    "In this case, the third-party entity along with its e id is revoked.",
    "The patient's EMR in the database is also deleted.",
    "The patient then generates new secret keys, encrypts the EMR fragments with these keys, and re-saves them in the database."
  ]
}